<paragraph id="E8403669FF8CFFF0FE041E6486D1B68F" blockId="27.[413,901,1129,1156]" box="[413,901,1129,1156]" pageId="27" pageNumber="826">
<heading id="B3088105FF8CFFF0FE041E6486D1B68F" box="[413,901,1129,1156]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="27" pageNumber="826" reason="5">
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF8CFFF0FE041E6486D1B68F" authority="(Westwood, 1834)" baseAuthorityName="Westwood" baseAuthorityYear="1834" box="[413,901,1129,1156]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Microvelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="826" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchella">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFF8CFFF0FE041E6487CBB68F" bold="true" box="[413,671,1129,1156]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="826">Microvelia pulchella</emphasis>
(Westwood, 1834)
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E8403669FF8CFFF0FF591E928746B783" blockId="27.[160,1156,1183,1416]" pageId="27" pageNumber="826">
This species of veliid water strider is known from the 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FF8CFFF0FCA11E928680B6B3" box="[824,980,1183,1208]" name="Virgin Islands" pageId="27" pageNumber="826">Virgin Islands</collectingCountry>
, reported from St. Thomas, as well as 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FF8CFFF0FE311ECF8778B6D0" box="[424,556,1218,1243]" name="Puerto Rico" pageId="27" pageNumber="826">Puerto Rico</collectingCountry>
and other Caribbean Islands (
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF8CFFF0FC131ECF8142B6D0" author="Barber HG" box="[906,1046,1218,1243]" pageId="27" pageNumber="826" pagination="264 - 441" refId="ref22283" refString="Barber HG. 1939. Insects of Porto Rico and the Virgin Islands: Hemiptera-Heteroptera (excepting the Miridae and Corixidae). Sci Surv Porto Rico Virgin Islands. 14: 264 - 441." type="journal article" year="1939">Barber 1939</bibRefCitation>
; de Kort- Gommer and Nieser 1969). We found this taxon in saline pools in and around the mangroves at Magens Beach, and in both Spring Road ghut and Cats and Chickens ghut, as well as in the water hazards at the Herman E. Moore Golf Course in St. Thomas. 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF8CFFF0FF391F418462B76E" author="Barber HG" box="[160,310,1356,1381]" pageId="27" pageNumber="826" pagination="264 - 441" refId="ref22283" refString="Barber HG. 1939. Insects of Porto Rico and the Virgin Islands: Hemiptera-Heteroptera (excepting the Miridae and Corixidae). Sci Surv Porto Rico Virgin Islands. 14: 264 - 441." type="journal article" year="1939">Barber (1939)</bibRefCitation>
reported the congeneric 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF8CFFF0FDCA1F418618B76E" authority="Uhler, 1894" authorityName="Uhler" authorityYear="1894" box="[595,844,1356,1381]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Microvelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="826" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robusta">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFF8CFFF0FDCA1F418793B76E" box="[595,711,1356,1381]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="826">M. robusta</emphasis>
Uhler, 1894
</taxonomicName>
from St. Thomas also, but it was not collected in our surveys.
</paragraph>
